humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states that there are 19 positive lymph nodes out of 21 examined (19/21) in the right axillary contents. This corresponds to the AJCC staging system's N3a category, which indicates metastasis in 10 or more axillary lymph nodes. Therefore, the N stage is N3.

humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient's pathology report indicates that there are 19 out of 21 lymph nodes involved with metastatic carcinoma in the right axillary contents. This corresponds to a pathologic N stage of N3a (pN3a) based on the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) staging system.
